gomodel:SYNGO_5464  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1-3: in COS-7 cells, SNK (PLK2) interacts with, and can degrate, postsynaptic protein SPAR (SIPA1L1). Further, SNK inhibits SPAR-mediated reorganization of actin cytoskeleton.\n\nFigure 4: immunofluorescence stainings in cultured hippocampal neurons showed overexpressed SNK is localized to dendritic spines and induces loss of SPAR, PSD-95 (DLG4), and Bassoon (BSN).\n\nFigure 5: overexpressed SNK induces loss of dendritic spines and increased filopodia in cultured hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 6: Synaptic activity induces endogenous SNK and leads to loss of SPAR and PSD-95.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary hippocampal neurons were prepared as described (1).\" PMID:11502259 --> \"For spine morphology studies, hippocampal primary neuronal cultures prepared from embryonic day (E) 18-19 rat embryos were plated at high density\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5464" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

